    <article>
        <h2>articles vs sections</h2>
        <p>Reference<br><br><a href="https://www.shecodes.io/athena/60553-when-to-use-section-or-article-in-html"><img src="shecodes.png" alt="Shecoes.io" style="width:200px;"><br><br></a>In HTML, section and article are both used for semantic grouping of content, but there is a slight difference between them.<br>
        Use section when you want to group content semantically based on a thematic grouping. <br>It is typically used when you have different sections of content on a page.In contrast, use article when you want to represent an independent, self-contained piece of content that can be reused on its own, without any other context. <br>It is typically used for blog posts, news articles, forum posts, etc.</p>
    </article>
